{
  "text": "Self-assessed functional status is documented using the Late Life Function and Disability Instrument [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The instrument includes 16 tasks representing a broad range of disability indicators that assesses both frequency of doing a task and perceived limitation. The instrument uses a scale from 0 to 100, with higher scores indicating higher levels of function. The scale has strong concurrent and predictive validity with physical performance [CITATION_3] .",
